         <t:abstract>
            <t:ab>
             The <t:foreign xml:lang="gez">Maṣḥafa qandil</t:foreign> is the ritual for the Unction of the Sick in the Ethiopian Church. Each of its seven sections consists of the following elements:
             the lighting of a wick, a supplication, an epistle, the Trisagion, the Prayer of the Gospel with incensing and a <t:foreign xml:lang="gez">mǝsbāk</t:foreign>, a Gospel reading and a prayer.
               This record corresponds to <t:bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/UTJXIDZV"><seg type="journalArticle"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Chaine1913Qandil"/><title level="a">Le rituel éthiopien - Rituel de l'Extrême-Onction (Rédaction de Galawdewos)</title><title level="j">Bessarione</title><editor><forename>Marius</forename><surname>Chaîne</surname></editor><date>1913</date><biblScope unit="volume">17 [29]; 18 [30]</biblScope><biblScope unit="page">420-451; 12-41</biblScope><note type="tags"><note type="tag">bm:Chaine1913Qandil</note></note><note type="tag">bm:Chaine1913Qandil</note></t:bibl> and the church editions, e.g.
